{"id": 231235854, "title": "8 'secret' Windows 11 features that you should know", "text": "Windows 11 introduces numerous features that can enhance productivity and streamline your workflow. Some of them are so useful that you\u2019ll wish you had known them earlier. Here are ten lesser-known but incredibly useful features you should explore:Scrolling inactive windowsThis feature allows you to scroll through a window without bringing it to the foreground. Enable it by navigating to Settings > Bluetooth & devices > Mouse and toggling on \"Scroll inactive windows when hovering over them.\"Shake to minimize and maximizeEnable \"Aero shake\" via Settings > System > Multitasking > Title bar window shake. Shaking a window minimizes all other open windows. Doing the same maximises them at once.GodMode folderGodMode provides a centralized location for all system settings. Create a new folder on your desktop and rename it to GodMode.{ED7BA470-8E54-465E-825C-99712043E01C}. The folder icon will change to the Control Panel icon, giving you quick access to various settings.Clipboard historyClipboard history allows you to store multiple copied items. Activate it in Settings > System > Clipboard and press Windows key + V to access your clipboard history. You can also pin a clipboard item if needed. Focus sessionsFocus sessions help minimise distractions. Access this via the Clock app or Settings > System > Focus. It provides timers, progress tracking, and break intervals to enhance productivity.Virtual desktopsSeparate work and personal tasks using virtual desktops. Press Windows key + tab to open Task View and create a new desktop. Switch between desktops easily using the same shortcut or three finger mouse gesture.Screen recording with Snipping ToolThe Snipping Tool in Windows 11 now supports screen recording. Launch it with Windows key + shift + S, select the camcorder icon, and start recording. It captures both system audio and microphone inputs.Insert emojis and symbolsQuickly access emojis, symbols, and GIFs with Windows key + . (period) or Windows key + ; (semicolon). This feature also includes clipboard history for easy pasting.", "summary": "Windows 11 introduces ten lesser-known but incredibly useful features that enhance productivity and streamline workflow, including scrolling inactive windows and screen recording with Snipping Tool.", "url": "https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-tips/8-secret-windows-11-features-that-you-should-know/articleshow/110819134.cms", "image": "https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/resizemode-4,width-1280,height-720,msid-47529300/47529300.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 13:10:16", "author": "TOI TECH DESK", "authors": ["TOI TECH DESK"], "language": "en", "source_country": "IN", "sentiment": 0.102}